}}</ref>，翻译自1611年出版的[[钦定版圣经|钦定版圣经]]<ref>Barton, John (2002–12). The Biblical World, Oxford, UK: Routledge. {{ISBN|978-0-415-27574-3}}.</ref><ref>North, Eric McCoy; Eugene Albert Nida ((2nd Edition) 1972</ref>）；这本书于1629年在[[荷兰|荷兰]]印制。随后，鲁尔又翻译了[[馬可福音|馬可福音]]，并于1638年出版此书<ref>{{id}} [http://sejarah.sabda.org/sejarah/bio_ruyl.htm Biography of Ruyl] {{Wayback|url=http://sejarah.sabda.org/sejarah/bio_ruyl.htm |date=20210224130746 }}</ref><ref>{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/514364/Albert-Cornelius-Ruyl|title=Encyclopædia Britannica: Albert Cornelius Ruyl|encyclopedia=Britannica.com|accessdate=2014-01-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019171117/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/514364/Albert-Cornelius-Ruyl|archivedate=2013-10-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[马来西亚政府|马来西亚政府]]曾于2007年作出禁止非穆斯林使用“安拉”一词的法令，但{{tsl|en|High Court of Malaya|马来西亚高等法院|马来西亚高等法院}}在2009年撤销了该法律，并裁定其违宪。虽然安拉一词被用于指代基督教的上帝已有超过四百年的历史，但马来西亚的天主教周刊{{tsl|en|The Herald (Malaysian Catholic Weekly)|先锋报 (马来西亚天主教周刊)|先锋报}}使用“安拉”一词来称呼上帝仍在当代引起了争议。马来西亚政府对法院的裁决提出上诉，马来西亚聯邦高等法院宣布在听取上诉前将暂停执行原判决。2013年10月，上诉法院判决支持政府的禁令<ref>{{cite news |title= No more 'Allah' for Christians, Malaysian court says |first= Simon |last= Roughneen |url= http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Asia-Pacific/2013/1014/No-more-Allah-for-Christians-Malaysian-court-says |newspaper= [[The_Christian_Science_Monitor|The Christian Science Monitor]] |date= 14 October 2013 |accessdate= 2013-10-14 |archive-date= 2020-11-22 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201122151139/https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Asia-Pacific/2013/1014/No-more-Allah-for-Christians-Malaysian-court-says |dead-url= no }}</ref>2014年年初，马来西亚政府在马来亞半岛没收了300多本使用安拉一词指代上帝的圣经<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-25578348|title= BBC News - More than 300 Bibles are confiscated in Malaysia|publisher= BBC|date= 2014-01-14|accessdate= 2014-01-14|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140125052310/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-25578348|archivedate= 2014-01-25|dead-url= no}}</ref>。然而，马来西亚聯邦的两个地區[[沙巴|沙巴]]和[[砂拉越|砂拉越]]并没有禁止非穆斯林使用安拉一词<ref name="settle">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyexpress.com.my/news.cfm?NewsID=87900|title=Catholic priest should respect court: Mahathir|newspaper={{tsl|en|Daily Express (Sabah)||Daily Express}}|date=2014-01-29|accessdate=2014-01-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110085352/http://www.dailyexpress.com.my/news.cfm?NewsID=87900|archivedate=2014-01-10|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.theborneopost.com/2014/03/29/worship-without-hindrance/|title= Worship without hindrance|author1= Jane Moh|author2= Peter Sibon|newspaper= {{tsl|en|The Borneo Post||The Borneo Post}}|date= 2014-03-29|accessdate= 2014-03-29|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140329094134/http://www.theborneopost.com/2014/03/29/worship-without-hindrance/|archivedate= 2014-03-29|dead-url= no}}</ref>。这两个地區没有颁布禁令的主要原因是使用安拉一词代指神或上帝的用法由来已久，而且当地印制的《圣经》多年来在砂拉越和沙巴广泛流传，并未受到限制<ref name="settle"/>。除此之外，这两个地區也被没有类似马来西亚的[[伊斯兰教法|伊斯兰教法]]<ref name="10-point"/>。

作为对一些媒体的回应，马来西亚政府出台了“十点方案”（又称十点解决方案），以避免可能产生的信息混乱和误导<ref>{{cite web|url= http://aliran.com/web-specials/bahasa-malaysia-bibles-10-point-solution/|title= Bahasa Malaysia Bibles: The Cabinet's 10-point solution|date= 2014-01-25|access-date= 2020-10-08|archive-date= 2014-12-27|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20141227150117/http://aliran.com/web-specials/bahasa-malaysia-bibles-10-point-solution/|dead-url= no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.thestar.com.my/News/Nation/2014/01/24/Najib-Kalimah-Allah/|title= Najib: 10-point resolution on Allah issue subject to Federal, state laws|newspaper= [[星报_(马来西亚)|星报]]|date= 2014-01-24|accessdate= 2014-06-25|archive-date= 2017-10-11|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20171011174422/http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2014/01/24/najib-kalimah-allah/|dead-url= no}}</ref>。十点方案符合马来西亚政府分别与砂拉越和沙巴签订的[[十八点协议|十八点协议]]和[[二十点协议|二十点协议]]的精神<ref name="10-point">。
